subject: RFC: Use a static data model for redfish
commitMessage:
RFC: Use a static data model for redfish

This commit adds a static data model for bmcweb Redfish. It is believed
that using a static data model will make validating correctness easier,
and increase code readability.

The static data model were build using the from redfish schemas using
the code added to the scripts directory.

Current status:
Only one response (service_root) has been altered to use the static
datamodel

We're prettymuch in the noise here.

> The uncompressed disk size shrank by a small amount

we should be looking at compressed size.  The command I use for this is:
gzip -c $BBPATH/tmp/work/s7106-openbmc-linux-gnueabi/obmc-phosphor-image/1.0-r0/rootfs/usr/bin/bmcweb | wc -c

replace s7106 with whatever your platform is.

I'd be really surprised if this ended up in a binary reduction in size.

> And the response time did not change a meaningful amount

I'm glad you measured that, but I'm guessing any optimizations are going to be deep in the noise here.
